Follow

There are a ton of quick wins with AI video for social that most brands are sleeping on.

Instead of worrying about trying to make AI creations indiscernible from meticulously shot and planned ones, consider that frivolity and speed is the virtue of AI video. AI enables rapid prototyping.

The framing of "AI Slop" isn't helpful or accurate here. Quick, silly videos are instead best understood as "gags", per the concept in comedy. 

In this format, you're not necessarily crafting in-depth and meaningful stories, but chucking out a bunch of one-liners and seeing what sticks. If something briefly amuses or entertains an audience, it's doing far more than most pre-roll ads on YouTube.

Sora is great for this. Not only can you spin up quick, silly videos in seconds, but you can also generate meaningful brand impressions on the social aspect of the platform itself.

If you're looking for a starting point, think about cultural references you can tie your brand to that would be too expensive to produce with a camera, and test it out!
